gay men, previously exploited teens reentering foster care, navigating nonmonogamous relationships, and more. Each chapter offers concrete, comparative case formulation that depicts culturally responsive work with LGBTQ+ people by LGBTQ+ social workers. These diverse vignettes showcase a range of life experiences and explore how factors like religion, age, and immigration status affect social work practice. The case studies in this volume integrate best-practice standards and interventions, social work ethics and competencies, and clinical and critical theories. Queer Social Work is a progressive pedagogical tool that provides a forum for marginalized communities and individuals as well as the committed practitioners who serve them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aSexual minoritiesxSocial conditions. 0aSocial work with sexual minorities. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / General.2bisacsh1 aArgüello, Tyler M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBowers, Pam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrandon-Friedman, Richard A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDziengel, Lake, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarris-Jackson, Tameca N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKattari, Shanna K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKronner, Henry W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLa Torre, Joanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeitch, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLewis, Terrence O., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMehrotra, Gita R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vo